<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>Factorise the following quadratic expression:
<me>
{x^2+13 x+40}
</me>
</p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We want to factorise:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{x^2+13 x+40}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the coefficient of <m>x</m> and the constant term.
</p>

<p>
The coefficient of <m>x</m> is <m>{13}</m> and the constant term is <m>{40}</m>.
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Find two numbers that:
</p>

<ul>
<li>multiply to give <m>{40}</m></li>
<li>add to give <m>{13}</m></li>
</ul>

<p>
The numbers are <m>{8}</m> and <m>{5}</m> because:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{8} \times {5} = {40}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
{8} + {5} = {13}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Write the factorised form:
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x + {8})(x + {5})
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\left(x+5\right) \left(x+8\right)</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>